          <td id="content-bg"><table align="left" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" >
              <tr>
                <td class="heading">Welcome to Queens College</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td height="50"></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td align="center"  class="content"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                    <tr>
                      <td align="left"><div>
	<img align="right" alt="" src="http://www.queenscollegemun.ca/ckfinder/userfiles/images/Dr_-Alex-Faseruk.jpg" style="width: 225px; height: 300px; padding-left:10px;" />It is with great pleasure that I welcome you to the website of Queen&rsquo;s College, an institution founded in 1841. Our college is dedicated to providing a high quality theological education to men and women of faith, for not only ordained ministry, but also to those who wish to enhance their baptismal ministry.</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	Whether you are visiting the website for the first time or as a regular guest, I pray that your visit will be a blessing to you. Please take some time to explore our website and to see what our college community can offer to you.</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	We are a theological college of the Anglican Church of Canada located on the campus of Memorial University. The college is jointly governed by the three Anglican dioceses of the province of Newfoundland and Labrador.</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	The most important part of our mission is to offer both full-time and part-time theological programs in theology to individuals preparing for ordination. In recent years, we have offered programs to people not seeking ordination. While we were founded as a theological institute for Anglican ministry, we now welcome people of all faith who wish to become educated in theology.</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	If you have any questions about our degree, associate and diploma programs, please contact us at 709-753-0116.</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	With every blessing,</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	The Rev. Dr. Alex Faseruk</div>
<div>
	Provost and Vice-Chancellor</div>
<div>
	<img alt="" src="/ckfinder/userfiles/images/AFC-logo-wordmark-tag-rgb.gif" style="width: 360px; height: 144px; float: right;" /></div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	&nbsp;</div>
<div>
	<p>
		&nbsp;</p>
	<p>
		&nbsp;</p>
	<p>
		<strong>Statement of Institutional Effectiveness</strong></p>
	<div>
		The Board of Commissioners of the Association of Theological Schools in the United States and Canada requires schools publish a statement regarding the school&rsquo;s educational effectiveness.&nbsp; Queen&rsquo;s College notes that we have graduates of the following programs who are engaged in active ministry in not only Newfoundland and Labrador, but in the Canadian Armed Forces, the United States and several foreign countries: &nbsp;</div>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<div>
				Master of Divinity</div>
		</li>
		<li>
			<div>
				Master of Theological Studies&nbsp;</div>
		</li>
		<li>
			<div>
				Bachelor of Theology</div>
		</li>
		<li>
			<div>
				Bachelor of Theology by Distance</div>
		</li>
		<li>
			<div>
				Associate in Theology</div>
		</li>
		<li>
			<div>
				Diploma in Theology and Ministry</div>
		</li>
		<li>
			<div>
				Certificate and Continuing Education programs.</div>
		</li>
	</ul>
</div>
